The overturning streamfunction in the subpolar North Atlantic and its low-frequency variability are largely determined by the SWMT13,14,30. The SWMT is the transformation of water from one density class to another due to buoyancy losses and gains at the sea surface. The SWMT is calculated by integrating the surface density flux over outcrop regions in each density bin as follows2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
