				\begin{document}$${{\rm{AMOC}}}\left(y,\, \sigma,\, t\right)=-{\int }_{{z}_{{{\rm{bot}}}}}^{0}{\int }_{{x}_{w}}^{{x}_{e}}H\left({\sigma }^{{\prime} }\left(x,\, y,\, z,\, t\right)-\sigma \right)v\left(x,\, y,\, z,\, t\right){dxdz}$$\end{document}AMOCy,σ,t=−∫zbot0∫xwxeHσ′x,y,z,t−σvx,y,z,tdxdzwhere H is the Heaviside function, σ’ represents the density field, x is longitude, y is latitude, z is depth, t is time, σ is the density at which the streamfunction is calculated, and v is the Meridional velocity. The zonal integral is performed across the Atlantic Ocean from the western boundary (xw) to the eastern boundary (xe), and the vertical integral is performed from the ocean bottom (zbot) to the sea surface. Density referenced to 2000-m depth (σ2) is used as the vertical coordinate (in units of kg m−3, after subtracting 1000 kg m−3). We also remap the AMOC streamfunction in density space into depth space using the time and zonally averaged depth of each density layer following previous studies31,32.
